threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects instances of svchost.exe running with an unusual or uncommon command line parameter by excluding known legitimate or common patterns.
This could point at a file masquerading as svchost, a process injection, or hollowing of a legitimate svchost instance.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Schedule Task Creation From Env Variable Or Potentially Suspicious Path Via Schtasks.EXE
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects Schtask creations that point to a suspicious folder or an environment variable often used by malware

match_context.values: @{Product=Microsoft\xae Windows\xae Operating System; CurrentDirectory=C:\Users\Bruno\Desktop\; OriginalFileName=schtasks.exe; Hashes=SHA1=85E046DE3C2DE1B4C85E57BA00CF7151B3D59F24,MD5=D857FA7279E2861199583474C17A1C6C,SHA256=DDDE64F0F55751763C1BCD53DE9CDFFC0D725D45A8476464A2A0422661813004,IMPHASH=44E70F20C235C150D75F6FC8B1E29CD1; Description=Task Scheduler Configuration Tool; EventID=1; ParentCommandLine="C:\Users\Bruno\Desktop\file.exe"; CommandLine="schtasks" /create /tn "Windows Update" /sc ONLOGON /tr "C:\Users\Bruno\AppData\Roaming\Windows Data\Updater.exe" /rl HIGHEST /f; FileVersion=10.0.22621.1 (WinBuild.160101.0800); ParentImage=C:\Users\Bruno\Desktop\file.exe; IntegrityLevel=High; Image=C:\Windows\System32\schtasks.exe; Company=Microsoft Corporation}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious DNS Query for IP Lookup Service APIs
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects DNS queries for IP lookup services such as "api.ipify.org" originating from a non browser process.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: ADS Zone.Identifier Deleted By Uncommon Application
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the deletion of the "Zone.Identifier" ADS by an uncommon process. Attackers can leverage this in order to bypass security restrictions that make use of the ADS such as Microsoft Office apps.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious Network Connection to IP Lookup Service APIs
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects external IP address lookups by non-browser processes via services such as "api.ipify.org". This could be indicative of potential post compromise internet test activity.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious Schtasks Schedule Type With High Privileges
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects scheduled task creations or modification to be run with high privileges on a suspicious schedule type

match_context.values: @{Hashes=SHA1=85E046DE3C2DE1B4C85E57BA00CF7151B3D59F24,MD5=D857FA7279E2861199583474C17A1C6C,SHA256=DDDE64F0F55751763C1BCD53DE9CDFFC0D725D45A8476464A2A0422661813004,IMPHASH=44E70F20C235C150D75F6FC8B1E29CD1; CurrentDirectory=C:\Users\Bruno\Desktop\; OriginalFileName=schtasks.exe; Product=Microsoft\xae Windows\xae Operating System; Description=Task Scheduler Configuration Tool; FileVersion=10.0.22621.1 (WinBuild.160101.0800); ParentCommandLine="C:\Users\Bruno\Desktop\file.exe"; CommandLine="schtasks" /create /tn "Windows Update" /sc ONLOGON /tr "C:\Users\Bruno\AppData\Roaming\Windows Data\Updater.exe" /rl HIGHEST /f; EventID=1; ParentImage=C:\Users\Bruno\Desktop\file.exe; IntegrityLevel=High; Image=C:\Windows\System32\schtasks.exe; Company=Microsoft Corporation}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects non-interactive PowerShell activity by looking at the "powershell" process with a non-user GUI process such as "explorer.exe" as a parent.
Detects the creation of scheduled tasks by user accounts via the "schtasks" utility.
